          <p class='first-para'>
            I did at least begin by responding to the amendment that would bring the matter before Parliament again and I ended on it. I concluded by saying that although the Tote is a public body under the 1963 Act&#x2014;let me make it clear that I am not departing from that&#x2014;there could be a query whether the Government were entitled to dispose of it without the approval of Parliament. That is what we are proposing to do. Where I contend with the amendment is that because we are seeking the authority of Parliament for this Act, it is not necessary to include the further reference to Parliament that the amendment proposes.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0659P0-07257'>
        <a name='S5LV0659P0_20040331_GCR_20'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-colin-moynihan' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040331_GCR_20' title='Link to this speech by Mr Colin Moynihan' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
