            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_484gc' title='Col. 484GC &mdash; HL Deb 31 March 2004 vol 659 c484GC' name='column_484gc' href='#column_484gc' rel='bookmark'>484GC</a>
            operation, in a sale on the open market, would then have to bring money into racing because it would have to pay for access to race courses and pictures. I n any case, we have always said that racing will be compensated in some way, and we still take that view. There is no possibility of holding a sale which would not bring some benefit to racing.
